title: Bearcat Men's Soccer prepares for big three game stretch starting Saturday
text:
Saturday, October 24, 2015 - 3:19:39 AM Local Sports Bearcat Men's Soccer prepares for big three game stretch starting Saturday 10/22/2015 (Updated 11:04:31 PM) The BU men's soccer team is tied with New Hampshire atop the America East conference standings and with three games left in the regular season. The Bearcats need to finish off those games strong. The first game is Saturday against last years final four participant UMBC. The Bearcats lost to the Retrievers last year 1-0 in Baltimore County. Now coming into this match, the Bearcats have been riding a lot of success with rookie of the week Harrison Weilbacher . The freshman had two assists in their 2-1 win over New Hampshire and has a total of 4 on the season. They got four big points on the road last week and around during this time of the season, it's about staying focused and completing your goals. Game time was switched from 7 pm to 1 pm on Saturday at the Events Center.
